Notes on the Stenus cirrus group, with description of two new species from China (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae)Abstract Two new species, Stenus zhangdinghengi sp. n., Stenus maoershanus sp. n.,of the Stenus cirrus group are described from South China, Guangxi Province. The male of Stenus fellowesi Puthz, 2003 and the female of Stenus huanghaoi Tang & Li, 2008 were discovered for the first time. Their diagnostic characters are illustrated and a key to the Chinese species of the Stenus cirrus group is provided.